      eyebrow="The short version"
      heading="How Do You Care for an African Grey Parrot?"
      badge="8 essentials · 90-sec read"
      items={[
        { stat: "60–80%", label: "Pellet Base", body: "Feed formulated pellets as the foundation, plus fresh veg and a little fruit — never seed-only, never avocado." },
        { stat: '48"', label: "Cage Height", body: "A single Congo needs at least 36\" W × 24\" D × 48\" H with ¾–1\" bar spacing in stainless steel." },
        { stat: "3–4 hr", label: "Daily Interaction", body: "Greys are intensely social — they need hours of attention and out-of-cage time, not just space." },
        { stat: "UV-B", label: "Light + D3", body: "Full-spectrum UV-B on a 10–12 hr cycle lets a Grey make the vitamin D3 it needs to absorb calcium." },
        { stat: "2–3×", label: "Baths a Week", body: "Regular bathing controls powder-down dander and keeps a Grey's feathers and skin healthy." },
        { stat: "Annual", label: "Avian Vet", body: "A yearly wellness exam catches illness a Grey instinctively hides until it is advanced." },
        { stat: "40–60 yr", label: "Lifespan", body: "An African Grey is a multi-decade commitment — plan a guardian for it in your estate." },
        { stat: "100%", label: "CITES Documented", body: "Every C.A.Gs Grey is captive-bred under CITES Appendix I — never wild-caught, fully papered." },
      ]}
